A THREE-CAR collision caused major tailbacks on the M8. M8 crash misery A THREE-CAR collision caused major tailbacks on the M8.The crash took place on the westbound carriageway at Hillington at around 8am.Two lanes were blocked as a result of the incident, leading to congestion and long tailbacks.Tailbacks stretched over the Erskine Bridge follwing the crash.Traffic Scotland issued updates throughout the morning, also tweeting pictures on the congestion. 